1) Debian on VirtualBox(Karvinen 2021)
                 VirtualBOx allows a safe, isolates practice environment.
                 Download Debian ISO, create VM with proper memory/disk settings.
                 Disk partiotining only affects the virtual disk.
                 Update system and install tools for security and usability.
2) Command line basics
                 Navigate directories: pwd, ls, cd.
                 Read files: cat
                 Administrative actions: sudo
                 Pipes and redirection allow combining commands.
                 man helps read documentation and learn independently.
                 Understanding terminal output is key for problem solving.
3) Can't Fish - Network Connectivity
                  ping 1.1.1.1 tested connection
                  Enabled network and received replies
                  disabled network, no replies received
4) Local Only -Port Scanning
                  Installed nmap and ran sudo nmap -Alocalhost
                   most of the ports closed hence no active network services
5) Daemon Scan - Apache Server
                  Installed and started Apache web server.
                   Re ran nmap and port 80 was opened
6) Over the wire Bandit Levels 0-4
                   Connected via SSH, solved first 5 levels.
                    Taska used linux commands: list files, read hidden files, handle unusual names, identify file types.
